app.note:
Consonants are frequently doubled after anusvāra in this inscription and the text thus needs no emendation. It is, however, possible that the composer's intent was avicchinnān nikhāya, as found in the Kolāṟu grant of Vīra-Coḍa (
49-62 39 , line 8). Line 10 of the Korumelli grant of Rājarāja II (
), reads avichchinnan nikhāya, which Fleet emends to avicchinnān nikhāya.

div.p:
Reported with discussion in
12-13 . Edited from the original plates by V. Venkayya(
), with estampages and translation (skipping the legendary and historic genealogy up to line 36). The present edition by Dániel Balogh is based on a collation of Venkayya's edition with his rubbings. No image of the seal is available.
